        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3158356692" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11502387719000241378">The point of this book is to pay attention to early signs and to trust your &quot;intuition.&quot; Okay, what are the early signs about this book? <br/>-Endorsement of the author&apos;s expertise by Oprah. This is a red flag. You may like Oprah&apos;s taste in literature, but her track record on scientific facts is not so good. <br/>-Lots of anecdotes, no rigorous evaluation. Another red flag.<br/>-The anecdotes seem very cherry-picked. For example, a mother is worried about sending her child into surgery and the child dies. Exce</span>
  <span id="freeText11502387719000241378" style="display:none">The point of this book is to pay attention to early signs and to trust your "intuition." Okay, what are the early signs about this book? <br />-Endorsement of the author's expertise by Oprah. This is a red flag. You may like Oprah's taste in literature, but her track record on scientific facts is not so good. <br />-Lots of anecdotes, no rigorous evaluation. Another red flag.<br />-The anecdotes seem very cherry-picked. For example, a mother is worried about sending her child into surgery and the child dies. Except I would imagine that roughly 99% of mothers are worried about sending their children into surgery, so what is the predictive value of that? Another red flag.<br />-The author brags an awful lot. Enough red flags.<br /><br />So, I decided to follow the author's advice and run away.</span>
