              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9878116899059048571">Forgot to add this to my &quot;read&quot; shelf when I joined Goodreads until I saw that Tori is reading it. This book did change my life and years after reading it, there are many points that remain vivid in my memory and I actually recall them fairly regularly. Although the grim reality of what women in particular face in the sense of being targets on a daily basis is made quite clear through the book and scared me, that wears off while the insights gained have changed my perspective on protecting mysel</span>
  <span id="freeText9878116899059048571" style="display:none">Forgot to add this to my "read" shelf when I joined Goodreads until I saw that Tori is reading it. This book did change my life and years after reading it, there are many points that remain vivid in my memory and I actually recall them fairly regularly. Although the grim reality of what women in particular face in the sense of being targets on a daily basis is made quite clear through the book and scared me, that wears off while the insights gained have changed my perspective on protecting myself. A few key things that I learned from de Becker include: be very wary of anyone who makes unnecessary promises, if something feels wrong but you cannot put your finger on it - something is wrong - so act on your gut feelings, and my favorite is that it is much better to be perceived as rude than to end up as a victim. Predators use women's perceived social obligation to be courteous against them. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9878116899059048571" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

