<div id="review_31611952" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/31611952" />
    <a title="❀Aimee❀ Just one more page..." class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1463934-aimee-just-one-more-page"><img alt="❀Aimee❀ Just one more page..." src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1430971362p2/1463934.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/31611952?book_show_action=true">Aug 30, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="❀Aimee❀ Just one more page..." class="user" itemprop="url" name="❀Aimee❀ Just one more page..." href="/user/show/1463934-aimee-just-one-more-page">❀Aimee❀ Just one more page...</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1463934-aimee-just-one-more-page?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1463934-aimee-just-one-more-page?shelf=psychology-sociology">psychology-sociology</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1463934-aimee-just-one-more-page?shelf=safety">safety</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1463934-aimee-just-one-more-page?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer31611952" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15840948892859053617">I read this book years ago and never really wrote a review. THIS BOOK IS FASCINATING AND COULD LITERALLY SAVE YOUR LIFE. <br/><br/>Per the author&apos;s GR author page, <br/><blockquote>Gavin de Becker is an expert on the prediction and management of violence. He has served on President&apos;s Advisory Board at the U.S. Department of Justice and the Governor&apos;s Advisory Board at the California Department of Mental Health; he now runs a consulting firm which advises government agencies, universities, police departments, corporations,</blockquote></span>
  <span id="freeText15840948892859053617" style="display:none">I read this book years ago and never really wrote a review. THIS BOOK IS FASCINATING AND COULD LITERALLY SAVE YOUR LIFE. <br /><br />Per the author's GR author page, <br /><blockquote>Gavin de Becker is an expert on the prediction and management of violence. He has served on President's Advisory Board at the U.S. Department of Justice and the Governor's Advisory Board at the California Department of Mental Health; he now runs a consulting firm which advises government agencies, universities, police departments, corporations, and media figures on the assessment of threats and hazards.</blockquote><br /><br />He gives true examples in each section with people who either followed their gut instinct or didn't. He explains a bit as to WHY you should trust your gut instinct. The book was never boring for me since I was reading true gripping stories, or skills that could save me.<br /><br />There are sections on avoiding workplace violence (like people who come kill after being fired), how to deal with stalkers (truly different ideas than law enforcement will often preach), and how to recognize someone trying to manipulate you. I think the most helpful portion for anyone reading this was the section about sociopathic red flags. I grew up with my dad working as an acute psych inpatient unit nurse, so some of this I knew intuitively. It was interesting to see it put in a more usable way. <br /><br />The author has also written <i>Protecting the Gift</i>, which is a book about how to best protect your child from the violence they may encounter - from predators, to daycare selection, and other such things.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15840948892859053617" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


